HEADWORD: zygosity
<hw>zy*gos"i*ty</hw> <pr>(z⟦isl⟧*g⟦ocr⟧s"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The property of being either
homogeneous or heterogeneous with respect to the allelic genes
determining some hereditary trait in a diploid or polyploid organism; if
homogeneous, the organism is homozygous; if heterogeneous, it is
heterozygous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

